<br>
(OOC: Personally I don't think taking Late teens and early 20s against Reishicyben is a good idea.  He has a confirmed level range by friends from 28 to 29.  That would mean casters would be totally ineffective against it.  It's damage mitigation would also very heavily limit your own effect upon it, as monks rely on speed, not raw damage.  A single party of mid to high 20s would likely work, but even two parties of low 20s could easily get wiped out, not to mention could suffer from adds in the area.  If the parties are a little more buffed up by then, I may add my assistance.<br>
<br>
My recommendation:  You and Jamil camp the Sensate Reishi Elder that spawns near the Shadowhaven zone line.  It has a rare drop of a Fist of Wood.  The Reishi elder is about level 16 I would say.  While the fist of wood is a slight downgrade from a fist of horn, they still work extremely well (I still use my pair at the 22nd fist so I can attest to their battle worthiness), then go back there later in your career to pick of the Fists of Horn.  Personally, asking two full groups to wait ninety minutes for a spawn each time for a single item that will only benefit one person and is not an epic component seems a little bit much, but that's just me.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to be offensive or try to stop you from doing this, but consider this before you plan your foray... and remember monks used to have to do without these pretty toys, so you can definitely survive without them.)<br>
<br>
Edit: Also I would recommend both of you if you take my advice about the Reishi, get to about level 17 or so and join or make a bandit group while you take on the reishi elder.  This is an excellent place to get experience, if a bit dangerous and gives you something to do in between the six minute or so reishi spawn.  And Eki... You're concerned about the strength?  I would keep them more for the Stamina bonus.  Strength really adds only a minimal effect, but we really tend to need our Stamina... though with that weapon's speed... maybe the bonus is counter productive *smile* <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uwyntercrystalbow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wynter Crystalbow</A> at: 2/1/02 10:54:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udjfang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DJFang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#660000>(2/1/02 12:47:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Moon Raid (x-post from Brothers board)</span><hr size=1> Wynter and Eki, I appreciate both of your comments immensely. I knew this would be a tough area and the spawn time long, but with the other monsters that appeared in that area, I thought it would more than compensate for the wait time with gained experience. If the 'shroom is as challenging as you both have said, then perhaps it would be more prudent to wait. I suppose my overzealouness to obtain some of these items may have gotten the better of my judgement.<br>
